## Description
The&nbsp;**Extract Documents (DA-hotspot)** task allows to extract documents from the Digital Archiving 3 software service using the legacy Digital Archiving Endpoint configuration.

> Important

This is a legacy task created to support the migration to Digital Archiving 3 build 3.37 (January 2023 release). For all new applications, please refer to the latest version of the task:&nbsp;[Extract Documents (DA) On-Demand Workflow Task Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/extract-documents-da-on-demand-workflow-task-reference).

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the **Alias**&nbsp;field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- Click on the **Store &gt;&nbsp;Resource** field and select the Digital Archiving Hotspot resource to use.

> Note

For more information, see: [Digital Archiving Hotspot Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-hotspot-resource-reference).

- Enter the required&nbsp;**Input** parameters:

Field

Description

**Index pattern**

Name of the XML index file or a filename pattern (in glob format) to identify it&nbsp;(for example,&nbsp;*input.xml* or **.xml*).

> Important

If multiple files or no files match the index pattern, the task will fail.

**Query element**

Path to the XML tag containing the data to extract (for example:&nbsp;*/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/DA*)

**Category attribute**

Name of the input attribute&nbsp;containing the value of&nbsp;the requested document class (for example, *documentCategory*)

- Select the required&nbsp;**Output &gt; Content**; the possible values are:

**Metadata**: The payload is an XML file describing the metadata of the documents returned.

- **Metadata with embedded documents**: The payload is an XML file with the metadata and an additional tag containing the embedded documents&nbsp;embedded in Base64 format.

- **Metadata and documents**: The payload is a ZIP file containing the metadata XML file and the documents as separate files.

- **Documents**: The payload is the document (in case of single document returned), or a ZIP file containing one or more documents.

> Note

For more information on the structure of the DA3 Extractor's input and output, see:&nbsp;[Digital Archiving 3 Extractor Input and Output Structure](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-3-extractor-input-and-output-structure).
